articles.description: Russia would insist that part of the money is spent on the one-fifth of the country that Moscow's forces control, three sources told Reuters.
articles.title: Exclusive: Russia could concede $300 billion in frozen assets as part of Ukraine war settlement, sources say

articles.author: Vitalii Hnidyi, Valentyn Ogirenko
articles.description: Peace talks this week between Russia and the U.S. aimed at ending three years of war in Ukraine have not impressed front-line Ukrainian troops, who see no quick end to the fighting if Kyiv is left out of negotiations.
articles.title: Ukrainian soldiers dismiss Trump-Russia peace push

articles.description: But Arab states have yet to tackle critical issues like who will foot the bill for Gaza's reconstruction or how the Strip will be governed.
articles.title: Arab states scramble to counter Trump's Gaza 'Riviera' plan

articles.author: Timothy Gardner, Leah Douglas, Tim Reid, Valerie Volcovici
articles.description: Federal workers responsible for America's nuclear weapons, scientists trying to fight a worsening outbreak of bird flu, and officials responsible for supplying electricity are among those who have been accidentally fired in President Donald Trump's rush to lay off tens of thousands of workers.
articles.title: Fired and rehired: the dizzying confusion of Trump's government overhaul

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Financial Action Task Force (FATF), a global anti-money laundering watchdog, said on Friday it had removed the Philippines from its 'grey' list of countries under increased scrutiny, while it added Laos and Nepal to that list.
articles.title: The FATF global financial crime watchdog removes Philippines from 'grey' list

articles.author: Friederike Heine, Hakan Ersen
articles.description: Elon Musk-owned X has secured a German court motion to remove a judge overseeing a legal battle between the social media giant and two activist groups over sharing election data, a court document seen by Reuters on Friday showed.
articles.title: Musk's X gets German judge removed in battle over election data

articles.author: Jennifer Rigby, Lisa Baertlein
articles.description: The U.S. government's foreign aid freeze has upended the supply chain for medical products crucial for fighting diseases including HIV and malaria in some of the world's poorest countries, and life-threatening gaps could persist for months, according to two sources familiar with the sector.
articles.title: US aid freeze sows disruption in HIV, malaria product supply chains

articles.author: Jack Queen
articles.description: Luigi Mangione, the man accused of fatally gunning down health insurance executive Brian Thompson on a Manhattan street in December, is due in court in New York on Friday afternoon as he faces state murder and terrorism charges.
articles.title: Luigi Mangione due back in NY court on charges of killing health insurance CEO

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Syria's new President Ahmed al-Sharaa met China's ambassador to Damascus in the first public engagement between the two countries since the overthrow of Bashar al-Assad in December, Syrian state media said on Friday.
articles.title: Syria's new president meets Chinese envoy for first time since Assad's fall
